reviews.text:
Tasty and affordable cai fan they have. 1 fish filet and 1 steamed minced meat egg was only $5. Value for money.

Unfortunately, the food options were not a lot. And 3 stalls have been left empty for awhile.

ordered at ieat kitchen. ginger onion slice fish, It’s yummy, I like the strong ginger taste.

The coffee shop doesn’t have much food to choose from as some stalls are close.

Shop: ieat kitchen
Date of visit: 23 October 2021
Time of visit: Around 9plus pm
Item ordered: salty veg soup, sambal sotong rice, fu rong egg
Price SGD$19.40
Taste: CMI
Salty veg soup add chinese mushroom, has salty veg but soup and salty veg not salty.
Fu rong egg is ok.
Sambal sotong rice has 4 to 5 sotong kia leg head dont know go where, then 2 piece of sotong slice.
Dont bother unless u r very hungry and everything is not open.

Shop: Broadway coffee shop
Date of visit: 24 October 2021
Time of visit: Around 2plus pm
Items ordered: 2x teh c
Price: $2.60
Taste: CMI
Dont understand how can something as simple as teh c be so awful looking and taste. Time to change your 头手 .

Fairly new food court with the usual selection of local food and of course an Indian stall, western food, mala, dessert, zichar, economy rice and of course, drinks.

Quite crowded during meal times but that's cos it's so far, the only one in this immediate area.

Tried Bedok Corner Hokkien Mee. Had their Hokkien mee and white Carrot cake. Decent enough. Coffee shop is in a new Hdb estate but doesn’t seem to have sufficient ventilation. Will probably continue to takeaway food from there only even when dining restrictions ease.
